The PI (with collaborators) has obtained a nuber of results on boundary rigidity, lens maps, and local generation of entropy (in GAFA), on discretization in metric geometry and uniform approximation of metrics by graphs (in Proceedings of the AMS), on discretization for the Laplacian (in Journal of Spectral Theory), polyhedral FinslerSpaces with locally unique geodesics (in Polyhedral Finsler Spaces with locally unique geodesics), and on convolution of elliptic operators on mm-spaces (ready to submission). There are the most important results, there are some more unpublished results or results which are less impressive.

The PI works with two graduate students and a postdoc at Penn State. Another postdoc of the PI has completed his work and left for U Toronto last year.The PI also runs two seminars at Penn State. 

The PI has delivered a number of lectures at conferences and invited talk on his research supported by NSF, including: A Plenary Lecture, International Conference dedicated to 100 Years of A.D. Alexandrov, St. Petersburg;2012. Notre Dame University, a conference in the memory of J. Cao;
Conference: Systolic Geometry,, Topology, and beyond. Montpelier, France;
Conference:  Representations, geometry, dynamics and beyond, Euler institute, Russia; Conference: Geometry and Dynamics of Finsler Manifolds, Lumini, France; Conferences:  Inverse problems, Eiler institute, Russia, 2014;
A series of four talks at "Discrete networks: geometry, dynamics and PDEs" workshop at Pittsburgh University; invited seminar talks and colloquia at:  Colloquium and a Seminar Lecture, Montreal; Colloquium and a Seminar Lecture, MIT;  University of Pennsylvania, two talks, different years); University of Toronto; University of Washington; Courant Institute, NYU; Colloquium, Poly NY; Kent University, 2013; Steklov Institute, St. Petersburg; Tel Aviv University;  U. Chicago; Ohio State U.





